caption: Very good restaurant with perfect paella. Beautiful dine-in atmosphere and service and take-out dining is just as good. Try all the tapas, they are great.

I've been to Solea many times pre-Covid, but oddly, this was the most enjoyable visit of all. Our server was so attentive & pleasant, made an amazing cocktail, & the tapas, fresh & sooo delicious. A cozy & safe environment on a cold day. Try the Basque in the Sun & both Beef Tenderloin plates!
Great small plates for sharing.

Solea was a great experience. Due to Covid the restaurant had very few customers. The host and manager therefore gave us their utmost attention. We ordered 3 tapas which were served quickly and presented beautifully. The taste was amazing. I will definitely be there again.
Great tapas place and I try to go at least once every 6 months..

What an amazing experience Solea provided. It was cold and rainy so we sat inside. The dinning room had lots of space between tables. It felt like we had the place to our self. The staff was super friendly with lots of suggestions. We couldn’t decide what to order so we split a little bit of everything. I was really impressed with the quality of the tapas. I highly recommend the special sangria,they change it weekly. Looking forward to our next visit w my son. He loves Tapas and we feel safe to bring him with the entire staff masked up and constantly sanitizing everything.
Excellant sangria! Just had finger food but was great! Looking for to going again!!
The Duck was amazing but I loved everything I tried.
Visited without a reservation Saturday night. We were immediately seated. The food, service & atmosphere was awesome. We enjoyed our evening very much. Just go. Our waiter James was awesome as well.

Fantastic and strong cocktails like Missou and Mezcaliente. Tapas were wonderful including salmon with creamy dill, steak, patatas bravas, mushroom toasts (I'd prefer these warm to cold though). Postres were excellent too, as was the unobtrusive yet timely service. Pricey a bit ($200 for 3 people with 2 drinks each), but these poor restaurants need all they can get in this stupid plandemic universe!
Good food, drinks and nice outside sitting area

Came for dessert on our anniversary about 7pm on Sat eve after dinner elsewhere. The atmosphere was lovely and the food service was very good. I recommend the chocolate lava cake and the flan. Both perfectly satisfy a sweet tooth! I think some of the hostesses on Moody St are frazzled from pandemic seating,  customers coming from all directions, and, well, covid!. A few were very short with us instead of nice, helpful and welcoming. They are just looking to get the job done and let us know dinner customers take priority over dessert ones. Other than that, it was a perfect evening.
very good food

Wanted to love it as it always has a crowd and looks beautiful. Took abit to be seated as phones were prioritized over guests waiting to be seated  even with a reservation. Sangria was very underwhelming especially at the price point for both flavor and size of beverage. Veggies on underwhelming side.
Great food. Great atmosphere for outdoor pandemic dining. Also took information for contact tracing "just in case".
Good food

Mediocre. That is the best word to describe this bland tapas restaurant. We ordered a variety of dishes from meats to vegetarian and all of them were virtually tasteless and expensive. The waiter in our area was so clearly inebriated that he consistently tripped, fell and dropped drinks and food. I will never eat here again.
We had a good dinner at the outdoor table,they have a parking spot nearby the restaurant. The food was delicious 😋
The food and atmosphere were both amazing!!! Everything was fresh, hot, and prepared perfectly. We will absolutely go back again!
My favorite place to go for Tapas. Absolutely love their red sangria, and the Churros are to die for. Never a disappointment. Love this place!
Other than drinking out of plastic cups everything was wonderful.
My taste buds are still dancing on my tongue after experiencing the miraculous flavors of the creations I devoured!
Price was outrageous

given the good reviews we saw on google maps and opentable, we had high expectations. however, we thought it was generally disappointing save for a couple bright spots.  Drinks - 2/5 Items we tried: - blueberry ginger mojito -> could have used a stronger ginger beer and more lime juice. not much blueberry flavor either. the flavor was almost watery. - the intern -> had a good flavor profile, but the chile de arbol vastly overpowered everything else. could have been much better than it was!  Food - 3/5 Generally disappointing. Overall lacking in flavor. Below are the items we tried:  - plato de quesos -> cheese was okay. the bread was pretty good I thought. - ceviche -> overcooked, bland flavor - tortilla espanola -> overcooked, and the spicy creme fraiche was a little overpowering - albondigas de cordero -> by far the best tasting plate we had. the lamb was flavorful without being too strong, and the meat was very tender.  Dessert - 4/5 - churros con chocolate -> pretty good  Service - 2/5 - not very attentive. - everything was very slow. - the food came in a bizarre order. the drinks came after we were done with the cheese plate, right before everytihng else. the other three plates came all at once. - the waiter made some comments intending to be friendly but they came off wrong. he also couldn't figure out how to pronounce my girlfriend's name after seeing her name on the credit card (Olivia; shouldn't be too hard to say, but we figured he misread it). if there is any risk of mispronouncing a name, just don't say it!  I don't think we'll be coming back anytime soon.
Enjoyed all the tapas we ordered! Can’t wait to go back again!

This place was really amazing. I got takeout and every single dish was made to perfection. The staff was very friendly. 10/10 would return to eat there for sure. Everything was flavorful and sharing the tapas was a fun way to try a lot of things in one trip!
Very small the food
the cutlery was badly washed, I think they don't check if they are clean before wrapping them in the cloth napkins
Michael was our server on Saturday night, we tried out the new outdoor experience and he made it amazingly great!! Thank you!
Wonderful dinner and Sangria

Simply one of the worst dining experience. Period. · Took more than 20mins for the waiter to notice us and get water on the table. · Another 20mins or so for him to take our order; and when he couldn't figure out what I was talking about, he started rambling gibberish in a condescending tone. Honestly if you don't know what a “mocktail” is, maybe it's time you consider a different line of work. · We tried to give him the benefit of the doubt, maybe they're shorthanded or that our entrees just take longer. But after every other table that came in after us got served food(same as what we ordered) before us, we know this wasn't justifiable. We were the only asians there. Go figure. · The food finally arrived after what seemed to be like forever (over an hour at least). Food itself was okay; the sauce was on point, but definitely not worth the wait. And when I pointed out that they charged us for the bread basket that never came, the waiter had the nerve to insist the other way. He went on to blatantly snatch the bill out of my hand and stormed off. Just. Wow. · Also, note that this was outdoor seating in mid June during lunch time with such pathetic speed of service. My partner, who was patient enough to sit through the whole thing with me, got sunburned. He then kindly made the suggestion to the manager that they could consider installing some tents (like every other restaurant on the block). The manager rolled his eyes.  I've always wanted to try Solea since they seem to offer an interesting tapas menu, but after today I doubt we'll ever come back. There are numerous decent and legit Spanish/Latin American restaurants in town that bring good ambience, food and service together; sadly Solea isn't one of them.
Great restaurant good experience
Great thank you...

So went to Solea because I love Tapas and love trying new places. So... after hunting for parking and not finding any for a while walked to start the new experience. Well... clearly didn’t need a reservation because the place was half empty on a Friday evening. It took a while for someone to come to our attention but finally got a wine order in and forced the waiter to take some tapas orders as well and then it happened. The wait.  The pain of hunger started to set in. Hopes of some bread faded as no one even remembered we were here. Then more waiting and waiting. Thought about going home when it happened the first sign of food. But no. Not out table. Then more waiting until finally the first part of our order came out.  Lobster ravioli. Would have been great except you could tell it had been waiting for a while. Then we put our in for the rest of the food. Cutting it short it was already but still here waiting for the check so we can leave. Glasses still empty.

You put together a meal by selecting a number of different tapas dishes that you can share among your party. A great place in Waltham for tapas! We had cure meat and cheese plate plus yummy prawns, sausages, cauli flower, and more. Look at the pictures for ambience. The last picture was the churros! The drinks and food were all excellent. In addition they had a Wednesday special for 50% off paella! I would definitely recommend this restaurant. It was a nice atmosphere not cramped or too loud or too quiet. The service is also on point!

Very good tapas, been here several times and never disappointed by the food. Service tonight was a little on the slow side but still worth the trip for our group of 5. Must try the lamb meatballs and beef with apricot cream as well as the asparagus pasta and vegetable stew.
Ideal restaurant in the Waltham area to come for a date. Good amount of vegetarian options to choose from. Pretty good vegetable paella!

My favorite was the beef tenderloin with a brandy cream sauce; the sauce was so good my eyes rolled into my head. My friend is trying to decide which was her favorite: the tortilla, patatas bravas, the artichokes... She lived in Spain one summer and she tells me the food here is Legit. Its was all great, the garlic shrimp was a little salty for my taste but no complains here honestly. Kevin was very attentive and one of the best servers I've ever had the pleasure to be served by... the moment you walk through the door you instantly feel transported to the coastal villages of Spain. Excellent service and ambience. Food is delicious and varied. Great value. Don't pass up a chance to go!

Ive lived in Waltham for 7 years and Solea is my favorite restaurant in the city. I am never disappointed. The sangria is delicious, highly recommend the tostadas de alcachofas - I crave them on a regular basis - and the lobster ravioli is to die for. Happily come here every year on my birthday (and multiple times throughout the year). So good!
Fantastic food and amazing service!

First time here, absolutely delicious - very authentic and reasonably priced. We were referred here by a friend, and the visit definitely was worth the trip to Waltham. Service was great, the interior is beautiful - it will remind you of Spain!

My friend and I came after work on an early Saturday afternoon. Solea does not disappoint. First of all, I love the fact that they are a tapas bar that is open early instead of late afternoon. John the bartender was awesome, we had a porròn of cava to start with jamon, olives, and cheese. Everything delicious from the artichoke hearts to the garlic shrimp to the lamb chops, which were succulent beyond belief, I never had lamb like that before! The churros at the end of the meal were to die for! Love this place and will return! Salud 🥂

I happen to be strolling Moody st on a beautiful Saturday afternoon and decided to stop and check out Solea. I was immediately captivated by gorgeous decor... warm colors with multi colored hanging lanterns. The menu has great options for meat eaters and veggie eaters! I cant wait to come back on a girls night and order multiple Tapas to share and taste. I had Cintas con Espárragos, lemon pasta, basil pesto and asparagus. Delicious, tasty, tangy... just the right size for a light lunch, accompanied by Sangria of the day! Great treat for a Mom with a few hours to herself!

We decided to give Solea a shot since we were in the mood for tapas. Our server suggested ordering about three tapas per person, which worked out perfectly. We especially enjoyed the salmon, tostadas, and croquettes. Everything we ordered was delicious. We’d come back here again.

My girlfriend and I went here for dinner on a Friday night. Ambiance was beautiful. We got the paella, coles and the sangria flight. Delicious! Service was fantastic and friendly and quick. I’m on moody st all the time but had never been here before. The churros were warm and sugary too. I’ll definitely be here again!

I was so bummed as it was mine and my boyfriend's favourite restaurant, but we recently discovered Solea in Waltham and are so excited to have this food back in our lives! Everything on the menu is amazing (we've tried it all), but some of our favourites are the sangaria, tortilla espinola, basque frites, sauteed spinach, churros, and anything shrimp!

Also you can’t beat the ambiance with the tile, lanterns, and beautiful art! Recommend the Espinacas Gallegas (spinach with pine nuts and raisins), the empanadas, and the patatas bravas. And the sangria or ‘basque in the sun’ margarita are on point!
One of the best tapas bar in the area, the sangria flight is my personal favorite! I would also recommend the lobster ravioli’s, very tasty!

Have been here multiple times. Today the food took a little longer than desired, but our waiter/bartender was attentive and pleasant. Food was delicious as always. Really love this place :) strongly recommend!
Great food, nice atmosphere!

Delicious tapas, had the Pato Braseado (duck), the Salmon al la Piancha, and the Tostada's de Alcachofas (artichoke crostini), along with delicious sangria.  Great service, great atmosphere.

Husband and I tried Solea tonight. We were utterly disappointed. Of the five tapas we ordered, only one was decent. The rest were barely edible. The ceviche had clearly sat in the lime juice for many hours too long. The artichoke tostadas were soggy and made with ingredients from a can. And the sauce for the muscles resembled Campbell’s tomato soup. Worst meal we’ve had in a long time. If I could give less than one star I would.
Great selection, promt, professional service and reasonably priced, good food.

This place is amazing! Everything is so flavorful. I may not be using the correct terms but the mussels is massive dish, empanadas are big and flavorful, shrimp a la plancha is a must and the beef tenderloin never fails. It’s so hard to not order everything. SUPER bonus is the sangria and wine list. There is 3 different types and they offer a sangria flight if you can’t decide. The wine list is full of amazing Spanish wines. If your someone like me who enjoys wine but mostly knows the main types (Chardonnay, Sav Blanc, Albariño, Malbec  etc) it’s fun to try unique wines I’ve never heard of. Another great thing to know is they are VERY thorough with allergies. I have a dairy allergy and they are always very careful to make sure what I eat does not contain dairy.

The only word to describe this restaurant is INCREDIBLE. Every single thing I ate was absolutely phenomenal. The cheese bread was just the right amount of cheesey and the perfect slightly chewy (it’s tapioca bread) texture; the chicken empanada was the BEST I’ve ever had, with a delicious seasoning mixture and perfectly crispy shell; the pasta was melt in your mouth goodness, an al dente noodle with the perfect amount of asparagus and a delicious rich pesto; the short rib was SO tender with a light sweet sauce over top.  The food speaks for itself but the service is just as amazing! My bartender/server Sean was SO kind; he could see I’d had a long day and was very attentive and friendly without being overbearing. Just what I needed after a busy couple of days in meetings.  As if all this isn’t enough, the sangria was amazing! Honestly, the fact that this restaurant doesn’t have a perfect 5 star rating is appalling. I will certainly be back!
